The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 February is 37,124 (4,296.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 January, there were 2,167 new confirmed cases (250.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 January, there were 2,990 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 28% (823 fewer cases).
